    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html><html><head>\n<title>luvision.net</title>\n<meta name=\"keywords\" content=\"\">\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"\">\n<link type=\"image/x-icon\" rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"/logo.ico\">\n<meta http-equiv=\"content-type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\">\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"all\" href=\"css/style.css\">\n<script src=\"js/jquery.js\"></script> \n<script src=\"js/zoom.js\"></script>\n<style>\n\n.bigimg {\n\twidth: 1000px!important;\n\theight: 563px!important ;\n\tposition: fixed;\n\tleft: 0;\n\ttop: 0;\n\tright: 0;\n\tbottom: 0;\n\tmargin: auto;\n\tdisplay: none;\n\tz-index: 9999;\n\tborder: 10px solid #fff;\n}\n.mask {\n\tposition: fixed;\n\tleft: 0;\n\ttop: 0;\n\tright: 0;\n\tbottom: 0;\n\tbackground-color: #000;\n\topacity: 0.5;\n\tfilter: Alpha(opacity=50);\n\tz-index: 98;\n\ttransition: all 1s;\n\tdisplay: none\n}\n.bigbox {\n\twidth: 840px;\n\tbackground: #fff;\n\tborder: 1px solid #ededed;\n\tmargin: 0 auto;\n\tborder-radius: 10px;\n\toverflow: hidden;\n\tpadding: 10px;\n}\n.bigbox>.imgbox {\n\twidth: 400px;\n\theight: 250px;\n\tfloat: left;\n\tborder-radius: 5px;\n\toverflow: hidden;\n\tmargin: 0 10px 10px 10px;\n}\n.bigbox>.imgbox>img {\n\twidth: 100%;\n}\n.imgbox:hover {\n\tcursor: zoom-in\n}\n.mask:hover {\n\tcursor: zoom-out\n}\n.mask>img {\n\tposition: fixed;\n\tright: 10px;\n\ttop: 10px;\n\twidth: 60px;\n}\n.mask>img:hover {\n\tcursor: pointer\n}\n</style>\n<script>\n        $(function(){\n            /*\n             smallimg   // 小图\n             bigimg  //点击放大的图片\n             mask   //黑色遮罩\n             */\n            var obj = new zoom('mask', 'bigimg','smallimg');\n            obj.init();\n        })\n    </script>\n</head>\n\n<body>\n<ol id=\"menu\">\n  <li class=\"cur\"><a href=\"/\"><span>●</span> Home</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://www.luvision.net/list-publications.html\"><span>●</span> Publication</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"https://www.luvision.net/list-people.html\"><span>●</span> People</a></li>\n  </ol>\n<div id=\"container\">   <div id=\"site_title_big\"><a href=\"/\" style=\"text-decoration: none\"><img src=\"https://www.luvision.net/uploadfile/202103/16c0f3bba3a0ccf.png\" height=\"75\"></a></div>  <div class=\"heading_bg\">\n    <h2>Welcome</h2>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"tops\" style=\"padding:2px 34px; box-sizing: border-box;overflow: hidden; \">\n    <div class=\"image_front\"><img class=\"image_front_img\" src=\"https://www.luvision.net/uploadfile/202104/6a188587e32ea14.jpg\"></div>\n    <p><span style=\"color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-size: 14px;\"></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Dr. Lu FANG</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Professor, Dept. of EE, Tsinghua University</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Ph.D. (HKUST 2011), B.E. (USTC 2007)</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">E-mail: fanglu at tsinghua.edu.cn</span></p><p><br></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">We are a multidisciplinary research group working at the intersection of physical optics and artificial intelligence, aiming to push the frontiers of next-generation imaging and photonic computing. Our research is distinguished by joint design of optics, electronics, and algorithms, and by tightly integrating hardware-software and opto-electronic systems, enabling scalable, high-efficiency solutions for AI-native imaging and neuromorphic computing.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><br></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Several of our works have appeared as Cover Articles, Feature Articles, Spotlights, or Editors’ Picks.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Research on [Taichi Chip, Science 2024]&nbsp; and&nbsp; [FFM Learning, Nature 2024] was recognized&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">among</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">the \"Top 10 Scientific Advances in China\" (2024).</span></p><p><br></p>\t  \n\t  \n     </div>\n\n  <!--  <div class=\"image_centered\"></div>--> \n  <br>\n  <div class=\"newline_bg\" id=\"news\">\n    <h2>News</h2>\n  </div>\n  <style>\n.imgsss p img{display: initial !important;}\t\n\t\n</style>\n  <div class=\"list imgsss\"> <p><strong style=\"font-family: \">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong style=\"font-family: \">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Our group’s project code is available at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/THU-luvision\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(11, 113, 131); text-decoration-line: none;\">thu-luvision.github.io</a>.</strong><br></p><ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px 0px 0px 1.6em; color: rgb(1, 1, 1); font-family: Georgia, \" class=\" list-paddingleft-2\"><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>The work of&nbsp;</strong></span><a href=\"https://www.science.org/doi/10.1126/science.adl1203\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; text-decoration: none;\"><strong>Taichi</strong></span></a><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>is published in <em>Science</em></strong></span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>The work of <a href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-024-07687-4\" target=\"_blank\">FFM</a> is published in <em>Nature</em></strong></span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>The work of </strong></span><a href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41566-024-01466-3\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>WISE Imager</strong></span></a><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong> is published in <em>Nature Photonics</em></strong></span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>The work of <a href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-023-06558-8\" target=\"_blank\">ACCEL</a>&nbsp;</strong></span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>is published in <em>Nature</em></strong></span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>The work of <a href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-022-05306-8\" target=\"_blank\">Meta-Imaging</a> is published in <em>Nature</em></strong></span><br></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>The work of&nbsp;</strong></span><a href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41566-021-00796-w\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>DPU</strong></span></a><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong> is published in <em>Nature Photonics</em> (Cover Article)</strong></span></span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Aug 18, 2025, <span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"></span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">the work of \"RAFAEL\" is accepted by <em>Nature</em></span></span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>July 11, 2025, </strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">the work of \"PIN\" is accepted by <em>Nature Computational Science</em></span></span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>May 23, 2025, <span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"></span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">the work of \"DTU\" is accepted by <em>Nature Photonics</em></span></span></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>June 4, 2024</strong></span>, the work of \"Aop3D\" is accepted by <em>Science Advances</em></p></li><li><p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>May 20, 2024</strong></span>, the work of \"Wide-Field Wavefront Imager\" is accepted by <em>Nature Photonics</em></p></li><li><p><s